subject:
Advance your technical skills with the Microsoft Azure Virtual
 Trainings
body:
Hello from Microsoft! Having trouble viewing this email? | View as web page <[[https://info.microsoft.com/index.php/email/emailWebview?mkt_tok=MTU3LUdRRS0zODIAAAGB7GXQTpyg-1pDSoSP5CyB3FKFUgZEIOEp7osBnA-QVYNsm2qCCVbh71jcs4xgw6Z-es-LQxnHviwfKHlDl1g7vcUE4JNhbO4wSA77b6C-mhP59O3A4WwTcCP1&md_id=1261844]]> <[[https://azure.microsoft.com]]> <[[https://azure.microsoft.com]]> Microsoft Azure
Virtual Trainings Days

Learn new Azure technical skills and become Microsoft certified

As your organization adapts to new ways of working, learning, and achieving, get the technical skills you need to move forward with confidence at the Microsoft Azure Virtual Training Days. Learn how Microsoft Azure’s cloud service solutions can help your business stay up and running while overcoming challenges big and small, with learning available for every skill level. Regardless of where or what work needs to get done, Microsoft is here to help. Let’s move forward together.

Our technical experts will cover:

  • Preparation for the Microsoft Azure Fundamentals certification exam and after completion of the Microsoft Azure Virtual Training Day: Fundamentals you’ll be eligible to take the exam at no cost.
  • How to manage and maintain environments that span on-premises technology, multicloud services, and edge devices using Azure hybrid and muticloud solutions
  • The capabilities of cloud services and the vast array of Azure technologies.
  • Solutions and efficiencies in a feature-rich and virtually unlimited environment.

Join us at our upcoming virtual event:

Virtual Training Date Registration Link
Microsoft Azure Virtual Training Day: Implementing Hybrid Infrastructure January 31-February 1 REGISTER FOR VIRTUAL TRAINING

We look forward to seeing you there!

Microsoft Azure

subject: You may lose access to some of your third-party apps
body:
[image: Google]
On May 30, you may lose access to apps that are using less secure sign-in
technology


abdul.rafey7047@gmail.com
To help keep your account secure, Google will no longer support the use of
third-party apps or devices which ask you to sign in to your Google Account
using only your username and password. Instead, you’ll need to sign in
using Sign in with Google
<https://accounts.google.com/AccountChooser?Email=abdul.rafey7047@gmail.com&continue=https://support.google.com/accounts/answer/112802?rfn%3D1646361360139%26anexp%3Dnret-fa>
or other more secure technologies, like OAuth 2.0. Learn more
<https://accounts.google.com/AccountChooser?Email=abdul.rafey7047@gmail.com&continue=https://support.google.com/accounts/answer/6010255?rfn%3D1646361360139%26anexp%3Dnret-fa>
------------------------------
*What do you need to do?*

*Email software, like Outlook 2016 or earlier,* has less secure access to
your Gmail. Switch to Office 365, Outlook 2019 or newer, or any other email
software where you can sign in using *Sign in with Google*.
Learn more
<https://accounts.google.com/AccountChooser?Email=abdul.rafey7047@gmail.com&continue=https://support.google.com/accounts/answer/6010255?rfn%3D1646361360139%26anexp%3Dnret-fa>
You received this email to let you know about important changes to your
Google Account and services.
